<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-02-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-02-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="209" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d209">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-02-29"><hi rend="italic">February 29,
                                    1892</hi></date>. (Received March 2.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my note of the 25th November
                            last, and to your note of the 30th of the same month on the subject of
                            the charge of immigrants who are not permitted to land at Boston, I have
                            the honor to recall the matter to your attention and to express the hope
                            that I may be favored with a reply to my above-mentioned note at an
                            early date.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>